cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with single-image 3D reconstruction, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm presented in the paper, GenRe, is designed to capture more generic, class-agnostic shape priors, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of 2.5D representations, spherical shape representations, and 3D voxel-based representations, which are all related to computer graphics (cs.GR). The algorithm exploits the causal structure of how 3D shapes give rise to 2D images, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization of the algorithm to diverse novel objects, which is related to robotics (cs.RO).
